461 // Add info for Wasm-global-based relocation. ----
462 // 'GlobalIndex' is used for split dwarf, which currently relies on a few ----
463 // assumptions that are not guaranteed in a formal way but work in practice. ----
464 void DwarfCompileUnit::addWasmRelocBaseGlobal(DIELoc *Loc, StringRef GlobalName, 0
465 uint64_t GlobalIndex) { ----
466 // FIXME: duplicated from Target/WebAssembly/WebAssembly.h ----
467 // don't want to depend on target specific headers in this code? ----
468 const unsigned TI_GLOBAL_RELOC = 3; 0
469 unsigned PointerSize = Asm->getDataLayout().getPointerSize(); 0
470 auto *Sym = cast(Asm->GetExternalSymbolSymbol(GlobalName)); 0
471 // FIXME: this repeats what WebAssemblyMCInstLower:: ----
472 // GetExternalSymbolSymbol does, since if there's no code that ----
473 // refers to this symbol, we have to set it here. ----
474 Sym->setType(wasm::WASM_SYMBOL_TYPE_GLOBAL); 0
475 Sym->setGlobalType(wasm::WasmGlobalType{ 0
476 static_cast(PointerSize == 4 ? wasm::WASM_TYPE_I32 ----
477 : wasm::WASM_TYPE_I64), ----
478 true}); ----
479 addUInt(*Loc, dwarf::DW_FORM_data1, dwarf::DW_OP_WASM_location); 0
480 addSInt(*Loc, dwarf::DW_FORM_sdata, TI_GLOBAL_RELOC); 0
481 if (!isDwoUnit()) { 0
482 addLabel(*Loc, dwarf::DW_FORM_data4, Sym); 0
483 } else { ----
484 // FIXME: when writing dwo, we need to avoid relocations. Probably ----
485 // the "right" solution is to treat globals the way func and data ----
486 // symbols are (with entries in .debug_addr). ----
487 // For now we hardcode the indices in the callsites. Global indices are not ----
488 // fixed, but in practice a few are fixed; for example, __stack_pointer is ----
489 // always index 0. ----
490 addUInt(*Loc, dwarf::DW_FORM_data4, GlobalIndex); 0
491 } ----

569 // Construct a DIE for this scope. ----
570 void DwarfCompileUnit::constructScopeDIE(LexicalScope *Scope, 0
571 DIE &ParentScopeDIE) { ----
572 if (!Scope || !Scope->getScopeNode()) 0
573 return; 0
574 ----
575 auto *DS = Scope->getScopeNode(); 0
576 ----
577 assert((Scope->getInlinedAt() || !isa(DS)) && 0
578 "Only handle inlined subprograms here, use " ----
579 "constructSubprogramScopeDIE for non-inlined " ----
580 "subprograms"); ----
581 ----
582 // Emit inlined subprograms. ----
583 if (Scope->getParent() && isa(DS)) { 0
584 DIE *ScopeDIE = constructInlinedScopeDIE(Scope, ParentScopeDIE); 0
585 assert(ScopeDIE && "Scope DIE should not be null."); 0
586 createAndAddScopeChildren(Scope, *ScopeDIE); 0
587 return; 0
588 } ----
589 ----
590 // Early exit when we know the scope DIE is going to be null. ----
591 if (DD->isLexicalScopeDIENull(Scope)) 0
592 return; 0
593 ----
594 // Emit lexical blocks. ----
595 DIE *ScopeDIE = constructLexicalScopeDIE(Scope); 0
596 assert(ScopeDIE && "Scope DIE should not be null."); 0
597 ----
598 ParentScopeDIE.addChild(ScopeDIE); 0
599 createAndAddScopeChildren(Scope, *ScopeDIE); 0
600 } ----
601 ----
602 void DwarfCompileUnit::addScopeRangeList(DIE &ScopeDIE, 0
603 SmallVector Range) { ----
604 ----
605 HasRangeLists = true; 0
606 ----
607 // Add the range list to the set of ranges to be emitted. ----
608 auto IndexAndList = ----
609 (DD->getDwarfVersion() < 5 && Skeleton ? Skeleton->DU : DU) 0
610 ->addRange(*(Skeleton ? Skeleton : this), std::move(Range)); 0
611 ----
612 uint32_t Index = IndexAndList.first; 0
613 auto &List = *IndexAndList.second; 0
614 ----
615 // Under fission, ranges are specified by constant offsets relative to the ----
616 // CU's DW_AT_GNU_ranges_base. ----
617 // FIXME: For DWARF v5, do not generate the DW_AT_ranges attribute under ----
618 // fission until we support the forms using the .debug_addr section ----
619 // (DW_RLE_startx_endx etc.). ----
620 if (DD->getDwarfVersion() >= 5) 0
621 addUInt(ScopeDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_ranges, dwarf::DW_FORM_rnglistx, Index); 0
622 else { ----
623 const TargetLoweringObjectFile &TLOF = Asm->getObjFileLowering(); 0
624 const MCSymbol *RangeSectionSym = ----
625 TLOF.getDwarfRangesSection()->getBeginSymbol(); 0
626 if (isDwoUnit()) 0
627 addSectionDelta(ScopeDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_ranges, List.Label, 0
628 RangeSectionSym); ----
629 else ----
630 addSectionLabel(ScopeDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_ranges, List.Label, 0
631 RangeSectionSym); ----
632 } ----
633 } 0

635 void DwarfCompileUnit::attachRangesOrLowHighPC( 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
636 DIE &Die, SmallVector Ranges) { ----
637 assert(!Ranges.empty()); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
638 if (!DD->useRangesSection() || 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
639 (Ranges.size() == 1 && 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
640 (!DD->alwaysUseRanges(*this) || 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
641 DD->getSectionLabel(&Ranges.front().Begin->getSection()) == 0
642 Ranges.front().Begin))) { 0
643 const RangeSpan &Front = Ranges.front(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
644 const RangeSpan &Back = Ranges.back(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
645 attachLowHighPC(Die, Front.Begin, Back.End); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
646 } else ----
647 addScopeRangeList(Die, std::move(Ranges)); 0
648 } 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
649 ----
650 void DwarfCompileUnit::attachRangesOrLowHighPC( 0
651 DIE &Die, const SmallVectorImpl &Ranges) { ----
652 SmallVector List; 0
653 List.reserve(Ranges.size()); 0
654 for (const InsnRange &R : Ranges) { 0
655 auto *BeginLabel = DD->getLabelBeforeInsn(R.first); 0
656 auto *EndLabel = DD->getLabelAfterInsn(R.second); 0
657 ----
658 const auto *BeginMBB = R.first->getParent(); 0
659 const auto *EndMBB = R.second->getParent(); 0
660 ----
661 const auto *MBB = BeginMBB; 0
662 // Basic block sections allows basic block subsets to be placed in unique ----
663 // sections. For each section, the begin and end label must be added to the ----
664 // list. If there is more than one range, debug ranges must be used. ----
665 // Otherwise, low/high PC can be used. ----
666 // FIXME: Debug Info Emission depends on block order and this assumes that ----
667 // the order of blocks will be frozen beyond this point. ----
668 do { ----
669 if (MBB->sameSection(EndMBB) || MBB->isEndSection()) { 0
670 auto MBBSectionRange = Asm->MBBSectionRanges[MBB->getSectionIDNum()]; 0
671 List.push_back( 0
672 {MBB->sameSection(BeginMBB) ? BeginLabel 0
673 : MBBSectionRange.BeginLabel, ----
674 MBB->sameSection(EndMBB) ? EndLabel : MBBSectionRange.EndLabel}); 0
675 } ----
676 if (MBB->sameSection(EndMBB)) 0
677 break; 0
678 MBB = MBB->getNextNode(); 0
679 } while (true); 0
680 } ----
681 attachRangesOrLowHighPC(Die, std::move(List)); 0
682 } 0
683 ----
684 DIE *DwarfCompileUnit::constructInlinedScopeDIE(LexicalScope *Scope, 0
685 DIE &ParentScopeDIE) { ----
686 assert(Scope->getScopeNode()); 0
687 auto *DS = Scope->getScopeNode(); 0
688 auto *InlinedSP = getDISubprogram(DS); 0
689 // Find the subprogram's DwarfCompileUnit in the SPMap in case the subprogram ----
690 // was inlined from another compile unit. ----
691 DIE *OriginDIE = getAbstractScopeDIEs()[InlinedSP]; 0
692 assert(OriginDIE && "Unable to find original DIE for an inlined subprogram."); 0
693 ----
694 auto ScopeDIE = DIE::get(DIEValueAllocator, dwarf::DW_TAG_inlined_subroutine); 0
695 ParentScopeDIE.addChild(ScopeDIE); 0
696 addDIEEntry(*ScopeDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_abstract_origin, *OriginDIE); 0
697 ----
698 attachRangesOrLowHighPC(*ScopeDIE, Scope->getRanges()); 0
699 ----
700 // Add the call site information to the DIE. ----
701 const DILocation *IA = Scope->getInlinedAt(); 0
702 addUInt(*ScopeDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_call_file, std::nullopt, 0
703 getOrCreateSourceID(IA->getFile())); 0
704 addUInt(*ScopeDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_call_line, std::nullopt, IA->getLine()); 0
705 if (IA->getColumn()) 0
706 addUInt(*ScopeDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_call_column, std::nullopt, IA->getColumn()); 0
707 if (IA->getDiscriminator() && DD->getDwarfVersion() >= 4) 0
708 addUInt(*ScopeDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_GNU_discriminator, std::nullopt, 0
709 IA->getDiscriminator()); 0
710 ----
711 // Add name to the name table, we do this here because we're guaranteed ----
712 // to have concrete versions of our DW_TAG_inlined_subprogram nodes. ----
713 DD->addSubprogramNames(*CUNode, InlinedSP, *ScopeDIE); 0
714 ----
715 return ScopeDIE; 0
716 } ----

720 DIE *DwarfCompileUnit::constructLexicalScopeDIE(LexicalScope *Scope) { 0
721 if (DD->isLexicalScopeDIENull(Scope)) 0
722 return nullptr; 0
723 const auto *DS = Scope->getScopeNode(); 0
724 ----
725 auto ScopeDIE = DIE::get(DIEValueAllocator, dwarf::DW_TAG_lexical_block); 0
726 if (Scope->isAbstractScope()) { 0
727 assert(!getAbstractScopeDIEs().count(DS) && 0
728 "Abstract DIE for this scope exists!"); ----
729 getAbstractScopeDIEs()[DS] = ScopeDIE; 0
730 return ScopeDIE; 0
731 } ----
732 if (!Scope->getInlinedAt()) { 0
733 assert(!LexicalBlockDIEs.count(DS) && 0
734 "Concrete out-of-line DIE for this scope exists!"); ----
735 LexicalBlockDIEs[DS] = ScopeDIE; 0
736 } ----
737 ----
738 attachRangesOrLowHighPC(*ScopeDIE, Scope->getRanges()); 0
739 ----
740 return ScopeDIE; 0
741 } ----

956 /// Return all DIVariables that appear in count: expressions. ----
957 static SmallVector dependencies(DbgVariable *Var) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
958 SmallVector Result; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
959 auto *Array = dyn_cast(Var->getType()); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
960 if (!Array || Array->getTag() != dwarf::DW_TAG_array_type) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
961 return Result; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
962 if (auto *DLVar = Array->getDataLocation()) 0
963 Result.push_back(DLVar); 0
964 if (auto *AsVar = Array->getAssociated()) 0
965 Result.push_back(AsVar); 0
966 if (auto *AlVar = Array->getAllocated()) 0
967 Result.push_back(AlVar); 0
968 for (auto *El : Array->getElements()) { 0
969 if (auto *Subrange = dyn_cast(El)) { 0
970 if (auto Count = Subrange->getCount()) 0
971 if (auto *Dependency = dyn_cast_if_present(Count)) 0
972 Result.push_back(Dependency); 0

1000 /// Sort local variables so that variables appearing inside of helper ----
1001 /// expressions come first. ----
1002 static SmallVector ----
1003 sortLocalVars(SmallVectorImpl &Input) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1004 SmallVector Result; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1005 SmallVector, 8> WorkList; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1006 // Map back from a DIVariable to its containing DbgVariable. ----
1007 SmallDenseMap DbgVar; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1008 // Set of DbgVariables in Result. ----
1009 SmallDenseSet Visited; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1010 // For cycle detection. ----
1011 SmallDenseSet Visiting; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1012 ----
1013 // Initialize the worklist and the DIVariable lookup table. ----
1014 for (auto *Var : reverse(Input)) { 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1015 DbgVar.insert({Var->getVariable(), Var}); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1016 WorkList.push_back({Var, 0}); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1017 } ----
1018 ----
1019 // Perform a stable topological sort by doing a DFS. ----
1020 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1021 auto Item = WorkList.back(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1022 DbgVariable *Var = Item.getPointer(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1023 bool visitedAllDependencies = Item.getInt(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1024 WorkList.pop_back(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1025 ----
1026 assert(Var); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1027 ----
1028 // Already handled. ----
1029 if (Visited.count(Var)) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1030 continue; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1031 ----
1032 // Add to Result if all dependencies are visited. ----
1033 if (visitedAllDependencies) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1034 Visited.insert(Var); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1035 Result.push_back(Var); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1036 continue; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1037 } ----
1038 ----
1039 // Detect cycles. ----
1040 auto Res = Visiting.insert(Var); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1041 if (!Res.second) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1042 assert(false && "dependency cycle in local variables"); 0
1043 return Result; ----
1044 } ----
1045 ----
1046 // Push dependencies and this node onto the worklist, so that this node is ----
1047 // visited again after all of its dependencies are handled. ----
1048 WorkList.push_back({Var, 1}); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1049 for (const auto *Dependency : dependencies(Var)) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1050 // Don't add dependency if it is in a different lexical scope or a global. ----
1051 if (const auto *Dep = dyn_cast(Dependency)) 0
1052 if (DbgVariable *Var = DbgVar.lookup(Dep)) 0
1053 WorkList.push_back({Var, 0}); 0
1054 } 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1055 } ----
1056 return Result; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1057 } 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1059 DIE &DwarfCompileUnit::constructSubprogramScopeDIE(const DISubprogram *Sub, 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1060 LexicalScope *Scope) { ----

1071 } ----

1074 DITypeRefArray FnArgs = Sub->getType()->getTypeArray(); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1075 ----

1079 if (FnArgs.size() > 1 && !FnArgs[FnArgs.size() - 1] && 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1087 DIE *DwarfCompileUnit::createAndAddScopeChildren(LexicalScope *Scope, 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1088 DIE &ScopeDIE) { ----
1089 DIE *ObjectPointer = nullptr; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1090 ----
1091 // Emit function arguments (order is significant). ----
1092 auto Vars = DU->getScopeVariables().lookup(Scope); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1093 for (auto &DV : Vars.Args) 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1094 ScopeDIE.addChild(constructVariableDIE(*DV.second, *Scope, ObjectPointer)); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1095 ----
1096 // Emit local variables. ----
1097 auto Locals = sortLocalVars(Vars.Locals); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1098 for (DbgVariable *DV : Locals) 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1099 ScopeDIE.addChild(constructVariableDIE(*DV, *Scope, ObjectPointer)); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1100 ----
1101 // Emit labels. ----
1102 for (DbgLabel *DL : DU->getScopeLabels().lookup(Scope)) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1103 ScopeDIE.addChild(constructLabelDIE(*DL, *Scope)); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1104 ----
1105 // Track other local entities (skipped in gmlt-like data). ----
1106 // This creates mapping between CU and a set of local declarations that ----
1107 // should be emitted for subprograms in this CU. ----
1108 if (!includeMinimalInlineScopes() && !Scope->getInlinedAt()) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1109 auto &LocalDecls = DD->getLocalDeclsForScope(Scope->getScopeNode()); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1110 DeferredLocalDecls.insert(LocalDecls.begin(), LocalDecls.end()); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1111 } ----
1112 ----
1113 // Emit inner lexical scopes. ----
1114 auto skipLexicalScope = [this](LexicalScope *S) -> bool { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1115 if (isa(S->getScopeNode())) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1116 return false; 0
1117 auto Vars = DU->getScopeVariables().lookup(S); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1118 if (!Vars.Args.empty() || !Vars.Locals.empty()) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1119 return false; 0
1120 return includeMinimalInlineScopes() || 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1121 DD->getLocalDeclsForScope(S->getScopeNode()).empty(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1122 }; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1123 for (LexicalScope *LS : Scope->getChildren()) { 3 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1124 // If the lexical block doesn't have non-scope children, skip ----
1125 // its emission and put its children directly to the parent scope. ----
1126 if (skipLexicalScope(LS)) 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1127 createAndAddScopeChildren(LS, ScopeDIE); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1128 else ----
1129 constructScopeDIE(LS, ScopeDIE); 0
1130 } ----
1131 ----
1132 return ObjectPointer; 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1133 } 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1135 void DwarfCompileUnit::constructAbstractSubprogramScopeDIE( 0
1136 LexicalScope *Scope) { ----
1137 auto *SP = cast(Scope->getScopeNode()); 0
1138 if (getAbstractScopeDIEs().count(SP)) 0
1139 return; 0
1140 ----
1141 DIE *ContextDIE; ----
1142 DwarfCompileUnit *ContextCU = this; 0
1143 ----
1144 if (includeMinimalInlineScopes()) 0
1145 ContextDIE = &getUnitDie(); 0
1146 // Some of this is duplicated from DwarfUnit::getOrCreateSubprogramDIE, with ----
1147 // the important distinction that the debug node is not associated with the ----
1148 // DIE (since the debug node will be associated with the concrete DIE, if ----
1149 // any). It could be refactored to some common utility function. ----
1150 else if (auto *SPDecl = SP->getDeclaration()) { 0
1151 ContextDIE = &getUnitDie(); 0
1152 getOrCreateSubprogramDIE(SPDecl); 0
1153 } else { ----
1154 ContextDIE = getOrCreateContextDIE(SP->getScope()); 0
1155 // The scope may be shared with a subprogram that has already been ----
1156 // constructed in another CU, in which case we need to construct this ----
1157 // subprogram in the same CU. ----
1158 ContextCU = DD->lookupCU(ContextDIE->getUnitDie()); 0
1159 } ----
1160 ----
1161 // Passing null as the associated node because the abstract definition ----
1162 // shouldn't be found by lookup. ----
1163 DIE &AbsDef = ContextCU->createAndAddDIE(dwarf::DW_TAG_subprogram, 0
1164 *ContextDIE, nullptr); ----
1165 ----
1166 // Store the DIE before creating children. ----
1167 ContextCU->getAbstractScopeDIEs()[SP] = &AbsDef; 0
1168 ----
1169 ContextCU->applySubprogramAttributesToDefinition(SP, AbsDef); 0
1170 ContextCU->addSInt(AbsDef, dwarf::DW_AT_inline, 0
1171 DD->getDwarfVersion() <= 4 ? std::optional() 0
1172 : dwarf::DW_FORM_implicit_const, 0
1173 dwarf::DW_INL_inlined); ----
1174 if (DIE *ObjectPointer = ContextCU->createAndAddScopeChildren(Scope, AbsDef)) 0
1175 ContextCU->addDIEEntry(AbsDef, dwarf::DW_AT_object_pointer, *ObjectPointer); 0
1176 } ----

1229 DIE &DwarfCompileUnit::constructCallSiteEntryDIE(DIE &ScopeDIE, 0
1230 const DISubprogram *CalleeSP, ----
1231 bool IsTail, ----
1232 const MCSymbol *PCAddr, ----
1233 const MCSymbol *CallAddr, ----
1234 unsigned CallReg) { ----
1235 // Insert a call site entry DIE within ScopeDIE. ----
1236 DIE &CallSiteDIE = createAndAddDIE(getDwarf5OrGNUTag(dwarf::DW_TAG_call_site), 0
1237 ScopeDIE, nullptr); ----
1238 ----
1239 if (CallReg) { 0
1240 // Indirect call. ----
1241 addAddress(CallSiteDIE, getDwarf5OrGNUAttr(dwarf::DW_AT_call_target), 0
1242 MachineLocation(CallReg)); 0
1243 } else { ----
1244 DIE *CalleeDIE = getOrCreateSubprogramDIE(CalleeSP); 0
1245 assert(CalleeDIE && "Could not create DIE for call site entry origin"); 0
1246 addDIEEntry(CallSiteDIE, getDwarf5OrGNUAttr(dwarf::DW_AT_call_origin), 0
1247 *CalleeDIE); ----
1248 } ----
1249 ----
1250 if (IsTail) { 0
1251 // Attach DW_AT_call_tail_call to tail calls for standards compliance. ----
1252 addFlag(CallSiteDIE, getDwarf5OrGNUAttr(dwarf::DW_AT_call_tail_call)); 0
1253 ----
1254 // Attach the address of the branch instruction to allow the debugger to ----
1255 // show where the tail call occurred. This attribute has no GNU analog. ----
1256 // ----
1257 // GDB works backwards from non-standard usage of DW_AT_low_pc (in DWARF4 ----
1258 // mode -- equivalently, in DWARF5 mode, DW_AT_call_return_pc) at tail-call ----
1259 // site entries to figure out the PC of tail-calling branch instructions. ----
1260 // This means it doesn't need the compiler to emit DW_AT_call_pc, so we ----
1261 // don't emit it here. ----
1262 // ----
1263 // There's no need to tie non-GDB debuggers to this non-standardness, as it ----
1264 // adds unnecessary complexity to the debugger. For non-GDB debuggers, emit ----
1265 // the standard DW_AT_call_pc info. ----
1266 if (!useGNUAnalogForDwarf5Feature()) 0
1267 addLabelAddress(CallSiteDIE, dwarf::DW_AT_call_pc, CallAddr); 0
1268 } ----
1269 ----
1270 // Attach the return PC to allow the debugger to disambiguate call paths ----
1271 // from one function to another. ----
1272 // ----
1273 // The return PC is only really needed when the call /isn't/ a tail call, but ----
1274 // GDB expects it in DWARF4 mode, even for tail calls (see the comment above ----
1275 // the DW_AT_call_pc emission logic for an explanation). ----
1276 if (!IsTail || useGNUAnalogForDwarf5Feature()) { 0
1277 assert(PCAddr && "Missing return PC information for a call"); 0
1278 addLabelAddress(CallSiteDIE, 0
1279 getDwarf5OrGNUAttr(dwarf::DW_AT_call_return_pc), PCAddr); 0
1280 } ----
1281 ----
1282 return CallSiteDIE; 0
1283 } ----
